Real Madrid Wants Tevez as City Career Expires, Daily Mirror Says: Roundup

-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 
2011-10-10T08:47:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/real-madrid-wants-tevez-as-city-career-expires-daily-mirror-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Tevez Exit  Real Madrid wants to sign  Carlos Tevez  in the January
transfer window, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Tevez’s time at Manchester City is “effectively over”
after he didn’t respond to a request to enter as a substitute at
Bayern Munich, the Mirror said.  Arsenal Teen  Arsenal plans to sign 16-year-old Real Madrid midfielder
Jose Rodriguez to a five-year contract, the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  The Gunners are negotiating the compensation they will pay
the Spanish club, the Mirror said. Chelsea is leading the
pursuit of another Real player, 15-year-old striker Jose Angel
Pozo, the  Daily Mail  reported.  Ferguson Refusal  Manchester United coach  Alex Ferguson  rejected a request
for  Danny Welbeck  to join England’s Under-21 team for a game in
 Norway  today, the  Daily Mail  reported.  Ferguson didn’t want Welbeck to travel straight after
returning from Montenegro with the senior team, the Mail said.  Blackburn Fans  Blackburn co-owner Balaji Rao is paying travel expenses of
about 6,000 pounds ($9,360) for three fans who went to  India  to
see the team play, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  He made the gesture after meeting the fans at a party, the
Mirror said. Blackburn had already paid for nine supporters to
stay at a “posh” hotel in Pune, the Mirror said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Alex Duff in Madrid  at
 aduff4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
